The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Benson surgery

London: England umpire Mark Benson, who had left the field after suffering palpitations during the second Test between South Africa and India in Durban last month, will undergo a minor heart surgery. 

Benson was rushed to hospital after feeling unwell while officiating on the third day of the Test and was kept under observation. 

